                            <comment id="17948604" author="houston" created="Wed, 30 Apr 2025 23:22:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve tried a custom &quot;ResumableInputStream&quot; implementation that submits a new GetObject request with the already-read-bytes offset, and it outperforms the &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/aws/aws-sdk-java-v2/blob/master/services-custom/s3-transfer-manager/README.md&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;S3 TransferManager&lt;/a&gt; significantly. The TransferManager is about 5x slower than just doing it ourselves. So that&apos;s probably the best way forward, since the TransferManager also requires that we use the AsyncClient for AWS, which we don&apos;t currently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
